# 📐 Template Audit & Page Break Fix

## The Problem (What You See)

When your resume content exceeds 1 page:
- **Page 1**: Content runs off the bottom edge
- **Page 2**: Shows just a few leftover sections (Awards, Certifications, Publications, References) with **massive empty white space** below

This happens in **ALL 10 templates** because they all share the same broken layout logic.

---

## Root Cause Analysis

### 1. `getPageBreakSections()` is a no-op
[layoutHelper.ts:63](file:///c:/Users/pc/Desktop/seve/src/utils/layoutHelper.ts#L63) literally says:
```typescript
return { page1Sections: activeSections, page2Sections: [] }
```
It **always** puts everything on page 1 and **never** splits to page 2. The comment says "Let the browser decide" but the browser can't decide intelligently — it just cuts wherever the page boundary falls.

### 2. `resume-page` CSS has `min-height: 1123px` (A4) but `height: auto`
[index.css:780-785](file:///c:/Users/pc/Desktop/seve/src/index.css#L780-L785): The screen CSS makes the resume page **at least** 1123px (one A4 page) tall, but allows it to grow endlessly. So when you have 1.3 pages of content, it's a single 1400px-tall div. The browser then splits it at 1123px, leaving ~300px on page 2 — and the `min-height: 1123px` on page 2 creates all that blank space.

### 3. Page-break CSS exists but is incomplete
[index.css:802-816](file:///c:/Users/pc/Desktop/seve/src/index.css#L802-L816): There ARE `break-inside: avoid` rules for `.exp-entry`, `.edu-entry`, `.proj-entry`, `.preview-section-wrapper`, and headings. BUT:
- **Section wrapper divs** (the `mb-5` divs in templates like `<div className="mb-5">`) don't have any CSS class for page-break hints
- The small sections (awards, certifications, languages, references) use generic divs without `break-inside: avoid`

