### Change 3: Add `resume-section` class to ALL section wrappers in ALL templates

Every section wrapper `<div className="mb-5">` (or `mb-4`, `mb-3`) in every template needs a CSS class so we can target it for page-break avoidance.

**FILE**: [index.css](file:///c:/Users/pc/Desktop/seve/src/index.css)

**ADD** to the page break rules at the bottom (after line 810):

```css
/* Keep small sections (awards, certifications, languages, etc.) together */
.resume-section {
  page-break-inside: avoid !important;
  break-inside: avoid !important;
}

/* But allow large sections (experience, projects) to break between entries */
.resume-section-breakable {
  /* Allow breaks between entries, but not mid-entry */
}
.resume-section-breakable .exp-entry,
.resume-section-breakable .edu-entry,
.resume-section-breakable .proj-entry {
  page-break-inside: avoid !important;
  break-inside: avoid !important;
}
```

Then in **every template**, update section wrappers:

**For SMALL sections** (languages, skills, awards, certifications, interests, publications, references, volunteer) — change `<div className="mb-5">` to `<div className="mb-5 resume-section">`.

**For LARGE sections** (experience, projects, education) — change `<div className="mb-5">` to `<div className="mb-5 resume-section-breakable">`.

